INSERT INTO PRODUCT VALUES (6, 'Origin of Species book', 1, 89000, 'This book is the result of Darwin"s observations during his nearly five-year trip', 'The Origin of Species is the shortened name of the book On the Origin of Species by Natural Selection, or the Preservation of Predominant Strains in the Struggle for Survival (by Charles Darwin, published in 1859);. This is a rare science book that sold out its first 1,250 copies within a day and in a short time shook the world. This book is the result of Darwin"s observations during his nearly five-year voyage, from 1831 to 1836, aboard the Beagle around the world, along with his reflections and research for the next twenty years. , in which he poses the crucial question of transformationism or evolution. His books were published many times, revised and continuously updated until his death. Charles Robert Darwin (1809-1882); was a famous researcher in the field of naturalism. He was the one who discovered and demonstrated that all species evolved over time from common ancestors through the process of natural selection. If evolution was accepted by the scientific community and the general public in Darwin"s time, his theory of selection in the 1930s was seen as the primary explanation for this process, and is today widely accepted. became the basis for modern evolutionary theory. This discovery is the unifying theory for the biological sciences that can provide a rational explanation for species diversity.', 'https://i.pinimg.com/564x/ed/15/8e/ed158ed6f1a6134990066d3eb38db83c.jpg', 0, 5.0, 3, 20);
